---
import Layout from '../../../components/Layout.astro';
import { Code } from 'astro-expressive-code/components';
---

<Layout title="completion - CLI Reference" description="Generate shell autocompletion scripts for `azd app`.">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <nav class="text-sm mb-8">
      <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-neutral-500">
        <li><a href="/azd-app/" class="hover:text-blue-500">Home</a></li>
        <li>/</li>
        <li><a href="/azd-app/reference/cli/" class="hover:text-blue-500">CLI Reference</a></li>
        <li>/</li>
        <li class="text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">completion</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-yellow-100 dark:bg-yellow-900/40 rounded-lg border border-yellow-300 dark:border-yellow-700">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">⚠️ azd app completion</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">This command is not yet implemented.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Status</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
        The <code class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-700 rounded">azd app completion</code> command
        is planned but not yet available in the current version. Shell autocompletion will be added in a future release.
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100">What it will do:</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Generate shell autocompletion scripts for bash, zsh, PowerShell, and fish</li>
        <li>Enable tab completion for <code class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-700 rounded">azd app</code> commands and flags</li>
        <li>Suggest available services, commands, and options as you type</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100">Workaround:</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
        In the meantime, use <code class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-700 rounded">azd app &lt;command&gt; --help</code> 
        to see available flags and options for each command.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700">
      <div class="flex justify-between">
        <a href="/azd-app/reference/cli/" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">
          ← Back to CLI Reference
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
